President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has approved a disaster declaration for the State of Arizona, providing federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms and flooding from July 22 to July 24, 2021. The declaration allows for federal funding to be allocated to state, tribal, and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in Apache, Coconino, and Navajo counties. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for cost-sharing funding. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas, with additional designations possible in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.